(30, 30, 30)"><strong>I Was 48, My Lungs Were Holding Me Back, and </strong></span><span style="color: rgb(184, 92, 56)"><strong>I Had No Idea Until a Friend Told Me to Read This.</strong></span></p></span></div></div><div data-rid="d9168f98-8b3a-4b62-89e4-d536dccfc397" class="r-1bc05s5"><div data-rid="791d962f-ab7a-4464-9046-2d991fbcea25" class="r-pcjhjp alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>It wasn't my age. It wasn't my thyroid. It wasn't my<br>iron levels. It was something I'd been carrying in my<br>lungs for decades, and I had no idea.</p></span></div></div><div data-rid="e2678951-8085-4c9c-ba01-a061291b415c" class="r-1jvc2aa"><div data-rid="c0367474-6403-4c17-bc8a-0f9e7eb2727f" class="r-7a4k0z"><div data-rid="f65360e1-2706-4716-9e49-24f83f01532b" class="r-1d3kf1j alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><strong>KM</strong></span></div></div><div data-rid="33f3d44d-30fa-4f36-b400-69882de3ad4e" class="r-1j90x0"><div data-rid="de8b0028-20f0-45cb-91ed-d2d09da90eea" class="r-uv87pr"><div data-rid="2953c28a-b39f-4333-b2b2-aab151460abd" class="r-1a9jfkr alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">By Karen M. | February 2026</span></div></div><div data-rid="2a76792a-902b-4940-ac17-4c56a187d06e" class="r-1ob2ukc"><div data-rid="c65c25be-68aa-45d5-81b3-4e6c082becd6" class="r-1af1mgp alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">Verified BetterLungs® Customer</span></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="e7569134-a7ca-4840-9f6d-deea4a6ae996" class="r-1vqv368"><picture data-rid="bf888627-5257-4b59-8bf7-6e34d8e5875f" class="r-o66iwe"><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/812609dc-9cb5-487a-9184-b35df0d0e7e4?width=28" media="(max-width: 640px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/812609dc-9cb5-487a-9184-b35df0d0e7e4?width=28" media="(min-width: 641px) and (max-width: 1024px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/812609dc-9cb5-487a-9184-b35df0d0e7e4?width=28" media="(min-width: 1025px) and (max-width: 2400px)"/><img src="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/812609dc-9cb5-487a-9184-b35df0d0e7e4" class="r-18ucq3f" loading="eager"/></picture><div data-rid="4854a88f-2c05-4abc-8063-57cd4054094d" class="r-peenjo alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">Estimated 8-Minute Read</span></div></div></div><div data-rid="9562759b-b43f-4638-b607-77198a187d2e" class="r-1u4scbx"><picture data-rid="65236569-78da-46a0-81e3-75fbf7ca342f" class="r-1b92s4p"><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/0c7a65d8-4b07-4588-ab28-e3aa6df69714?width=706" media="(max-width: 640px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/0c7a65d8-4b07-4588-ab28-e3aa6df69714?width=706" media="(min-width: 641px) and (max-width: 1024px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/0c7a65d8-4b07-4588-ab28-e3aa6df69714?width=706" media="(min-width: 1025px) and (max-width: 2400px)"/><img src="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/0c7a65d8-4b07-4588-ab28-e3aa6df69714" class="r-64tn0z" loading="eager" alt="Woman sitting on a park bench watching children on swings along a winding path under oak trees at sunset."/></picture><div data-rid="22f48c95-c549-4c56-aad7-1162e26374a8" class="r-1pp2t7n"><div data-rid="fc7e1f24-2d62-447a-9c1a-4231e59f02ef" class="r-kqe6ly alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">I'm going to tell you something embarrassing.</span></div></div><div data-rid="0d353762-ec51-4dd4-9bd2-2ec10a8aa201" class="r-ksellg"><div data-rid="ebf156a3-5c46-475b-8e87-d10fd6b86641" class="r-1p7fxju alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Last spring, my 14-year-old daughter asked me to<br>go on a hike. Nothing crazy, a 2-mile loop at the<br>state park we used to visit every weekend when she<br>was little.</p></span></div></div><div data-rid="f81a0b1e-8ed1-4fe9-88ea-eebcadd65f0b" class="r-1tk30i6"><div data-rid="c57aebaa-4703-458e-aa99-2c55c5da55ee" class="r-v9m6jp alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><strong>I said no.</strong></span></div></div><div data-rid="7023a6eb-4384-4064-8240-bace4ad1046d" class="r-dy9bov"><div data-rid="43938c8e-9706-4054-8e0d-699f2af7157d" class="r-rz9ne6 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">Not because I was busy. Not because I didn't want<br>to. I said no because I was afraid I wouldn't be able<br>to keep up with her. That I'd be the one stopping<br>every 200 yards, hands on knees, pretending to<br>admire the view while I caught my breath.</span></div></div><div data-rid="03cfb3c2-8743-4ad0-aa67-4093c00d497b" class="r-1sbfhjj"><div data-rid="3dde7254-0931-4805-ab7b-31a21391d294" class="r-otta6 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">That was the moment I realized something was<br>really wrong.</span></div></div><div data-rid="d9f7c9d1-d2ae-425b-9bfb-5ddae55ff269" class="r-4wro0j"><div data-rid="cffb54e0-f2e0-473b-ae12-f479e0b712ec" class="r-59l1gx alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><strong>• • •</strong></span></div></div><div data-rid="3d0fa1e5-e928-49c9-82af-96390f39a8d7" class="r-1prs70c"><div data-rid="96a56d05-d9de-47f3-bbbe-f0ea82e2edc1" class="r-c3vazk alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><strong>It Started So Gradually I Almost<br>Didn't Notice</strong></span></div></div><div data-rid="fee6250b-938e-4960-bf96-cb6a3f94cc73" class="r-1un9q5q"><div data-rid="af81d129-425e-4375-b72f-be2380075d25" class="r-1pu6l56 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">Somewhere around 45, things shifted. I'd get<br>winded walking up the stairs. I'd need to "catch my<br>breath" after carrying groceries in from the car. I<br>started avoiding the second floor of the mall<br>because I knew the escalator would be faster than<br>my lungs could carry me.</span></div></div><div data-rid="c2e184bc-91fd-4d10-861d-22ca9a603c66" class="r-1ndjfjz"><div data-rid="a19f6970-f38b-4065-8f72-676aa643454e" class="r-dxsm3g alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">I didn't think of it as a breathing problem. I thought<br>of it as getting older.</span></div></div><div data-rid="e82525d2-9d13-4771-b8f4-e6124d648021" class="r-d7qe7r"><div data-rid="9e9b6cf7-451e-44e4-951a-b8944bd257a5" class="r-14f4g7o alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Everyone around me confirmed that. "You're almost<br>50, Karen. Things slow down." My doctor ran<br>bloodwork. Thyroid, iron, B12, vitamin D.<br>Everything came back normal. "You might just need<br>more sleep," she said.</p></span></div></div><div data-rid="901b7c0c-ef0b-4d00-8935-98a35375d1ac" class="r-1ipvdmh"><div data-rid="85ddfc1b-8927-4304-8875-d57a9af1b33f" class="r-11xd2ze alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">So I tried more sleep. A $200 weighted blanket.<br>Magnesium. No caffeine after 2pm. Morning walks.</span></div></div><div data-rid="3a5b3a58-6fbe-451c-a871-db81a1d0959f" class="r-v18frw"><div data-rid="e001a633-a536-4b31-859f-64fe70fd5c1e" class="r-16xvpw3 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">Nothing changed. I was still exhausted by 2pm. Still<br>winded going upstairs. Still the one at family<br>gatherings who sat down first, who waved everyone<br>else ahead, who said "I'll wait here" more times<br>than I could count.</span></div></div><div data-rid="253c82bd-7d3f-4874-ad11-0a1679c398f5" class="r-1qhz6qf"><div data-rid="1f3926ff-de33-4a21-a7c8-b626ad7a8f3a" class="r-4qp2ho"><div data-rid="f8916d63-c4fe-490a-af57-5f74e045dd0a" class="r-s6m99m alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><strong>💡 What I Didn't Understand</strong></span></div></div><div data-rid="f663a3b3-6de7-468f-96cc-cd2cc1127ad7" class="r-dxtix"><div data-rid="6c5a99b5-36ab-45e1-b327-205f9beede73" class="r-1t27ins alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">My bloodwork was fine. My heart was fine.<br>My hormones were fine. But nobody ever<br>thought to look at my lungs, because I<br>wasn't coughing, I wasn't wheezing, and I'd<br>never smoked a cigarette in my life.</span></div></div></div><div data-rid="c45e2fe8-95ff-456c-bce7-5df24af4dc44" class="r-1onqw5t"><div data-rid="f5a7fd65-5e75-4ef2-bd7d-d670c2508baa" class="r-1krnehh alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p><strong>The Text Message That Changed Everything</strong></p></span></div></div><div data-rid="475792b3-b9f6-4613-a151-3d4c234f2e10" class="r-1mgxhpw"><div data-rid="7cbbe394-951c-4238-8881-ef50cf2464fe" class="r-70a60r alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>In August, my sister-in-law Lisa sent me a link. No<br>context, just: "Read this. I think this is you."</p></span></div></div><div data-rid="09f056a1-3d4d-472b-8b6f-40bfacfe811e" class="r-1kfllzn"><div data-rid="a5725043-6dee-4bff-a6d2-1718623dc926" class="r-1d5a7pv alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>It was about respiratory congestion that builds up<br>silently over years. Not from smoking. From<br>everything else, the air we breathe,<br>environmental allergens, even decades of shallow<br>breathing patterns that let mucus and debris quietly<br>accumulate in the lower airways.</p></span></div></div><picture data-rid="e9e92efa-1bc8-4fb6-9001-51ed2fb60810" class="r-d8x0vj"><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/5de8bc70-ccb6-44da-a1ec-2e07e1c7b760?width=706" media="(max-width: 640px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/5de8bc70-ccb6-44da-a1ec-2e07e1c7b760?width=706" media="(min-width: 641px) and (max-width: 1024px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/5de8bc70-ccb6-44da-a1ec-2e07e1c7b760?width=706" media="(min-width: 1025px) and (max-width: 2400px)"/><img src="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/5de8bc70-ccb6-44da-a1ec-2e07e1c7b760" class="r-1ii1n5u" loading="eager" alt="Woman leaning on a kitchen counter reading a smartphone, coffee mug beside her with morning light through the window"/></picture><div data-rid="e01a2f7a-6483-4396-9c81-2f25b499f8e9" class="r-so9139"><div data-rid="ebd10478-be80-4bd6-86e7-883c29e9a0b8" class="r-1rm66yi alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">The article described it as "breathing at 60%<br>capacity without knowing it." Then it said<br>something that hit me like a truck:</span></div></div><div data-rid="fd44bc8b-134c-4418-80c5-28b7e3f00d0c" class="r-1qoiw7h"><div data-rid="76a6aa57-a551-4757-88af-139a78e10e77" class="r-ipb7sw"><div data-rid="f30a5e7a-4845-4305-b9e9-60a6348080c3" class="r-t6rhis alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>"Most people assume that if they can breathe, their lungs are fine. But decades of accumulated congestion can reduce your functional capacity so gradually that you never notice the decline, you<br>just think you're aging."</p></span></div></div></div><div data-rid="394c8820-5dd7-4103-b72d-1af7ea1e9177" class="r-1dbl72f"><div data-rid="1aed28c9-0486-46de-8f47-e9dd4df5c47b" class="r-12o3f4v alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">I read that three times. Then I called Lisa. "This IS<br>me."</span></div></div><div data-rid="54a58e33-4f8b-489f-8807-d68043901a49" class="r-1tmdiv9"><div data-rid="8f8659d5-e320-4c38-96cb-42b20a33d65e" class="r-51fkxt alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>The exhaustion. The breathlessness on stairs. The<br>low energy no amount of sleep could fix. What if it<br>wasn't aging? What if it was my lungs, slowly,<br>silently filling with years of buildup nobody<br>thought to check for?</p></span></div></div><div data-rid="ff28cf30-077e-4ef6-be6d-5d548f9cef54" class="r-zb4ic9"><div data-rid="58ba9aad-976b-4baa-9b3c-59268062841c" class="r-c3hxxh alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><strong>What I Found When I Started<br>Looking</strong></span></div></div><div data-rid="fac85484-7ad3-4d90-ae96-f91c0f166e6d" class="r-1uh6zkh"><div data-rid="fa10492f-6521-4d1b-a26f-4dc12bcbae9a" class="r-1z0yu36 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">Lisa told me she'd started taking a mullein and<br>chlorophyll tincture that a pharmacist had<br>formulated specifically for supporting respiratory<br>wellness. She'd been using it for six weeks and said<br>the difference was "like someone turned the volume<br>up on my breathing."</span></div></div><div data-rid="b203ed35-117b-48f6-aa97-585d3ea7ac5a" class="r-5qtvig"><div data-rid="e6bc96e6-9b91-4266-b316-a1fcaed0e464" class="r-1l5185o alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">I was skeptical. But Lisa isn't the type to fall for<br>nonsense. She's a nurse. And the formulator<br>wasn't some random supplement brand. It was Dr.<br>Chris Jackson, a Doctor of Pharmacy and former<br>U.S. Army Combat Medic who created it after<br>watching his own family members struggle with<br>respiratory issues.</span></div></div><picture data-rid="19bc6738-d959-4d0d-b059-db69909e3987" class="r-hmikzu"><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/1ebf1958-3981-4a14-a882-bd6339360095?width=706" media="(max-width: 640px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/1ebf1958-3981-4a14-a882-bd6339360095?width=706" media="(min-width: 641px) and (max-width: 1024px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/1ebf1958-3981-4a14-a882-bd6339360095?width=706" media="(min-width: 1025px) and (max-width: 2400px)"/><img src="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/1ebf1958-3981-4a14-a882-bd6339360095" class="r-x9f4r9" loading="eager" alt="Dr. Chris smiling in a white coat before a sign reading BETTER BRAND."/></picture><div data-rid="167091c4-5cd7-45eb-9d74-2ae9de51b9af" class="r-1xpgra9"><div data-rid="8efaefa0-77aa-4b0d-859d-a0b6c5a158e7" class="r-g819ui"><div data-rid="28505bb9-d4c9-4f36-9b89-d6114cfc2056" class="r-xecbh alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><strong>🧪 The Science Lisa Explained To Me</strong></span></div></div><div data-rid="3876a619-9cca-4734-939c-27104e2ee1a0" class="r-1up76kv"><div data-rid="021edd81-1903-456c-813e-b75319c203ad" class="r-b7q7t6 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Mullein, used for respiratory support for<br>2,000+ years, contains natural<br>compounds called saponins that help thin<br>and loosen old, stagnant mucus deep in the<br>airways.</p></span></div></div><div data-rid="1c349b62-68cc-4ef1-b75d-56e17f50c011" class="r-14xpvd7"><div data-rid="381b4187-a3ea-4e9e-bb79-6d387335f65a" class="r-18e8pcb alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Chlorophyll, the green pigment in plants,&nbsp;acts as a natural internal cleanser,<br>binding to trapped pollutants and debris so<br>the body can more easily clear them out.</p></span></div></div><div data-rid="b1ae3951-63ba-496c-bde3-d3e0ea807341" class="r-1vpaf2x"><div data-rid="ef5e1f9d-0602-40e5-acc4-bf16b2c52d12" class="r-16l7szt alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">Together: loosen the buildup, bind what<br>doesn't belong, and support your body's<br>natural clearance process.</span></div></div></div><div data-rid="b5205000-dda2-4656-9aad-a3ac1ace266e" class="r-szizu"><div data-rid="6fb85a7b-232b-4e32-85d0-ee4176f319a7" class="r-1aw35ca alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">The product was called BetterLungs® Mullein +<br>Chlorophyll. Over 1,000,000 people had tried it.<br>And it came with a 365-day money-back guarantee.</span></div></div><div data-rid="0c8486c2-6b29-4c77-8a12-a48738db31d9" class="r-ngw739"><div data-rid="c9095abd-e461-4142-8a4d-4ce2e4bd7407" class="r-1qczmoa alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>I figured, what did I have to lose?</p></span></div></div><picture data-rid="4ae8eeb3-381d-40ef-b852-fad585b8a42d" tabindex="0" class="r-i86jyq"><span class="patrol-sr-only">BetterLungs Mullein and Chlorophyll product package</span><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/5e8b2dab-4ec7-4b80-a55b-862fc3989302?width=706" media="(max-width: 640px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/5e8b2dab-4ec7-4b80-a55b-862fc3989302?width=706" media="(min-width: 641px) and (max-width: 1024px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/5e8b2dab-4ec7-4b80-a55b-862fc3989302?width=706" media="(min-width: 1025px) and (max-width: 2400px)"/><img src="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/5e8b2dab-4ec7-4b80-a55b-862fc3989302" class="r-88vujm" loading="eager"/></picture><div data-rid="30e38727-893d-49e9-8c86-7ba8d9ae76ec" class="r-wuwkly"><div data-rid="64831f44-b699-4048-81bd-576f5a69a2d8" class="r-11pljl1"></div><div data-rid="e0be6333-7dc8-456f-9ec1-b9a6bcd1afff" class="r-1gv1vri"><div data-rid="5c1b242f-96f0-4a60-954e-e48391e73111" class="r-193dwrb alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><strong>Try BetterLungs®<br>Mullein + Chlorophyll<br>Risk-Free</strong></span></div></div><div data-rid="220dc8d0-684e-41e5-913c-8d315ff7c241" class="r-19sqbq"><div data-rid="817b7248-d60c-46f0-9ba4-c12e05f422b2" class="r-zbmqq0 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">The pharmacist-formulated tincture trusted by<br>1,000,000+ customers.</span></div></div><div data-rid="b02a66ce-27b4-4cdf-91e8-541565f7c34d" class="r-ons0h0"><div data-rid="07ea0f62-9a03-4a7b-a12e-d1e93a553c3f" class="r-7ynv8q alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><strong>$34.95</strong></span></div></div><div data-rid="eee0f509-bdb6-484e-89c8-441cb5f77a34" tabindex="0" role="link" class="r-1wz9lz0"><div data-rid="37884645-ebbc-4e4c-98ae-74f141ceecb3" class="r-1oy71yz alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><strong>➜ Try BetterLungs® Risk-<br>Free</strong></span></div></div><div data-rid="7483f89b-21c4-439d-a388-9e7375839980" class="r-3ow78a"><div data-rid="27bd6436-48a0-455d-9fac-36f00cd2b61f" class="r-ozna9e alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">🛡️ 365-Day Guarantee · Free Shipping Available · Made<br>in USA</span></div></div></div><div data-rid="c3350b92-b1aa-4721-8497-86d1c05048b6" class="r-1r4jhzf"><div data-rid="5efd66b4-ec2c-4326-85cb-c56526b38120" class="r-1yob7af"><div data-rid="870603ad-6af5-4788-b499-762887d93fb4" class="r-1x5jg56 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">• • •</span></div></div></div><div data-rid="04de85e0-4cf1-4d7d-b734-33c1f89ee071" class="r-1blihkf"><div data-rid="45ebad91-4cbf-4dd6-b0b2-a0b140fad83b" class="r-1i1eqd5 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><strong>Week 1: "Wait… Is That What<br>Breathing Is Supposed to Feel<br>Like?"</strong></span></div></div><div data-rid="abc567bb-766f-4947-970b-5443a9eee6f2" class="r-iipj0m"><div data-rid="1bb4370f-625a-4f98-831e-a5b3c33fa849" class="r-f7c142 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>I took my first dropper on a Tuesday morning.<br>Mixed it into water, slightly earthy, slightly<br>minty. Not bad.</p></span></div></div><div data-rid="f7979081-ebe5-47b2-933d-c27df37cc91d" class="r-hy9953"><div data-rid="2596b883-ea7b-4b73-a851-782c95eae7e1" class="r-i0yg86 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">For three days, not much. Maybe slightly less<br>heaviness in my chest when I woke up, but I wasn't<br>sure if that was real or wishful thinking.</span></div></div><div data-rid="7f8caad7-578c-492b-b249-ebb7abb434d0" class="r-1fps6e"><div data-rid="53b80481-03e9-4153-bc6a-8452691f0a55" class="r-1bf1sfo alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Then Day 4. I woke up and took a breath. Not a<br>forced one, just a natural morning breath. And<br>something was... different. The breath went deeper.<br>It filled parts of my chest I didn't know had been<br>closed off.</p></span></div></div><div data-rid="d7bb560a-54b2-4281-ba06-803b1c8f4744" class="r-bnljhv"><div data-rid="43920a39-bdc7-4d1f-9fea-13683c1cfe9c" class="r-9zwir4 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">I sat on the edge of my bed and did it again. And<br>again.</span></div></div><div data-rid="3ed54af2-6147-4f1a-a51d-920fdac90a24" class="r-1cvk03w"><div data-rid="c98d2320-8a49-44ba-8cd4-4c8e9df83f1c" class="r-1kvif9n alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">I got a little emotional, honestly. I didn't realize how<br>shallow my breathing had become until I felt what a<br>full breath was supposed to feel like.</span></div></div><picture data-rid="3bfc031f-f42a-4e71-bf7c-adc03bd53b29" class="r-prjze5"><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/a06af5fb-5708-4f32-9daf-a4bb91a6e74d?width=706" media="(max-width: 640px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/a06af5fb-5708-4f32-9daf-a4bb91a6e74d?width=706" media="(min-width: 641px) and (max-width: 1024px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/a06af5fb-5708-4f32-9daf-a4bb91a6e74d?width=706" media="(min-width: 1025px) and (max-width: 2400px)"/><img src="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/a06af5fb-5708-4f32-9daf-a4bb91a6e74d" class="r-13in6uh" loading="eager" alt="Woman sitting on bed, hand over her chest and eyes closed, morning light through a nearby window."/></picture><div data-rid="9c889790-11fc-461b-abf6-e2f0acc11a68" class="r-13nnp0w"><div data-rid="484f062d-204c-430b-8115-89b137f13f38" class="r-qtyuim alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><strong>Week 2: The Energy Came Back<br>Like a Switch Flipped</strong></span></div></div><div data-rid="093d6642-af35-42f1-971e-98f8327d09ff" class="r-13llxbg"><div data-rid="fd03cb2a-cea1-45c6-8226-be35be38a4b8" class="r-bd0m2u alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">By the end of Week 2, the change wasn't subtle<br>anymore.</span></div></div><div data-rid="863d957f-b971-42ce-ab6c-3d7cb92314f6" class="r-b8a28n"><div data-rid="e3673df0-3b04-4c01-8844-9f1773256140" class="r-19wljlp alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>I walked the full loop at the grocery store, both<br>floors, without thinking about finding a bench. I<br>carried all the bags in one trip. I stayed awake past<br>9:30pm for the first time in months.</p></span></div></di